The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Saturday, April 03, 2004 				 BBC chairman
																								London, April 2 (Reuters): Maverick TV executive Michael Grade was named chairman of the BBC today as Britains public broadcaster recovers from an unprecedented judicial savaging of its pre-war Iraq coverage.																								The BBC has been through a battering. How much was its own making and how much was from outside, history will tell, Grade said. 
